It happens to English version too. 
I can reproduce the error in TigerSession class, if I typed "Tiger" in the Text 
field "Class name:" in the wizard "Create Enterprise Java Bean". But Tiger is 
not allowed for the bean class name. Instead, TigerBean should be used. Then 
everything works fine.

Charles Chen

Sending this to Naci (and team).  I beleive this originally comes from a problem
in the new bean wizard?

Problem fixed and check into the HEAD stream.  Should be availabe with the next
I-Build.  The wizard does validation checks and will not allow a user to create
a a bean without the Bean suffix, or into the default package.
in 20050513, I cannot create a EJB project. So I cannot verify this.
Changed Version field given new release numbering.
